abstract: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said Friday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine.
snippet: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said Friday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine.
lead_paragraph: Agence France-Presse, a global news agency based in Paris, said yesterday that it had settled its lawsuit against Google Inc., the online search engine, and would allow the Internet company to post news and photos from AFP journalists.

headline.main: News Agency and Google End Dispute Over Use of Material
headline.print_headline: News Agency and Google End Dispute Over Use of Material
